  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sushi Chef",
  "description": "<p><strong></strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 5-day work week (44 hours). Enjoy a structured schedule for true work-life balance.</p></li><li><p><strong>Master the Prep:</strong> Meticulously prepare, portion, and organize all fish, seafood, and ingredients.</p></li><li><p><strong>Craft the Foundation:</strong> Cook and season our signature sushi rice to perfection, every time.</p></li><li><p><strong>Create with Precision:</strong> Expertly craft sushi, sashimi, nigiri, and rolls that are consistently beautiful and delicious.</p></li><li><p><strong>Connect with Guests:</strong> Engage diners at the counter, present your creations confidently, and share your knowledge.</p></li><li><p><strong>Uphold Excellence:</strong> Maintain impeccable cleanliness and strict food safety standards at your station.</p></li><li><p><strong>Collaborate:</strong> Work in seamless rhythm with our kitchen and service teams for a flawless dining experience.</p></li><li><p><strong>Innovate:</strong> Contribute creative ideas for new menu items and seasonal specials.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Proven experience in a reputable sushi establishment.</p></li><li><p>Deep knowledge of Japanese cuisine, fish handling, and traditional techniques.</p></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p>EA Personnel R22110043 Tan Eng Kang</p><p>EA License 21C0430 A Dreamworks Company Pte Ltd</p>",
